story of Western Canada, where politicians often care more about extraction and growing the economy while destroying the very things the economy depends on. But that isn’t the whole story. Much like Canada’s universal health care, Saskatchewan is also the birthplace of some of the first provincial and national conservation laws, and home to an unsung and unlikely champion for the environment: a farmer with a twelfth-grade education and a really old van… In Protecting the Prairies, Andrea Olive provides a history of wildlife and land conservation in Saskatchewan told through the life story of environmentalist, naturalist, farmer, and former Minister of Environment and Resource Management Lorne Scott. This is a book that challenges and inspires us to be stewards of the environment in our own backyards and communities, and above all, to never be complacent when it comes to protecting the natural world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEnvironmentalismxPolitical aspectszSaskatchewan. 0aEnvironmentalistszSaskatchewanvBiography. 0aFarmerszSaskatchewanvBiography. 0aNaturalistszSaskatchewanvBiography. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh  aAldo Leopold.  aCanada Goose.  aCanadian politics.  aCrown lands.  aEnvironment Minister.  aEnvironmental Assessment Act.  aGrant Devine.  aLorne Calvert.  aLorne Scott.  aNDP.  aPFRA lands.  aRafferty-Alameda.  aRepresentative Area Network.  aRoy Romanow.  aSaskatchewan Wildlife Act.  aSaskatchewan Wildlife Habitat Protection Act.  aSaskatchewan.  aWallace Stegner.  aWildlife.  abirding.  abirds.  abluebirds.  aconservation easements.  aconservation.  aendangered species.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental policy.  afracking.  agame species.  agrasslands.  ahistory.  ahunting.  anatur